<font color="#FF0000">BRAVE METALS IN BAD WAR? ? ?</font><br>
<tt>Sun Feb 23 21:30:56 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
A good new site, congradulations to all.<br><br>
However, I beg to disagree with what sentiment I see and hear herewithin.  If you want to &quot;heal&quot; with those who did not walk the walk and talk the talk in the jungle, i.e. go to Nam, like me, the protestor, who did his 2 years of civilian service, or the resistors who fled, or the resistors who took amnesty, or those who didn't, or the MAJORITY of our generation who did not go 'in country&quot;, then don't put your metals IN OUR/MY FACE.  That is how this is hitting me.  So what that you got a marksmen award, or a valiant behavior award, in a war YOU should not have been in.  Metals, to me, are more propaganda and bull shit about how those above you continue to pull the wool over your eyes.  Come one friends, wake up. IF YOU AGREE THE WAR WAS WRONG THEN HOW CAN YOUR AWARDS BE RIGHT??<br><br>
It reminds me of doggy treats, you know, come on spot, sit up, kill, good dog, now here's your bon-bon. good spot.  I don't begrudge you your trophies, but I ask that you think about the rest of us &quot;out&quot; of country, and what they mean to us.  Yes, you have the right to be proud of being good soldiers, but please, seperate out the bull from the S....<br>
Metals for great and good soldiering is one thing, in a unjust and lousy war they take on a different meaning. I THINK THE METAL OR AWARD ITSELF, WHAT IT WAS GIVEN FOR, IS VERY IMPORTANT. SAVING LIVES-YES. KILLING CIVILIANS?-NO!!<br><br>
I hope this rocks a few and generates some thoughts, instead of the pavlovian YES SIR response.  Seems to me, and my woe-be gone shrink mind, that you use the metals to keep validating that you are ok, that you are not bad guys, that you want it both ways.  Hang on to your seats friends, but I can't say this anyother way:  Do the metals mean you were good baby killers?  Good Soldiers? or loyal Fido's?<br><br>
Guess this will get me some hate hits, but then again, I have never held my mud before, so why start now?  Isn't that what real dialogue is all about anyway?<br><br>
I'm ready.  P.S. I did my time too, and while it was nothing like yours, it also was more than most of my &quot;compadre's&quot;, and along with no G.I.Bill, no benefits, no prescriptions, no therapy groups at the local V.A., and no proclaimation saying I/we were right (except McNamara's snibbling confession, and recently, LBJ's tapes), no one to toot our horn.  Well. That's said.  As the song says: Hit me with your best shot(s). FIRE AWAY&quot;.   <br><br>
